<chapter>
	<title>Here they are... click for larger PNG versions!</title>

	<section>
		<title>Bart Verwilst</title>
		<body><p>Bart Verwilst is one of our desktop developers. He maintains Koffice, net-im, app-games, and most of the KDE user-end apps, and is our gentoo.org jabberserver admin. In this screenshot, you can see his KDE desktop which is using mosfet's liquid widgets theme:
		</p>
		<fig link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-verwilst-small.jpg" linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-verwilst.html"/>
		</body>
	</section>


	<section>
		<title>Mikael Hallendal</title>
		<body><p>Mikael Hallendal (Hallski) is a GNOME developer; here's his nice 1600x1200 GNOME desktop:</p>
		<fig linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-hallski.html" link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-hallski-small.jpg"/>
		</body>
	</section>

    <section>
		<title>Daniel Robbins</title>
		<body><p>Daniel Robbins (me!) is the Chief Architect of Gentoo Linux.  Here's my 1280x1024 desktop:</p>
		<fig linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-drobbins.html" link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-drobbins-small.jpg"/>
		</body>
	</section>

    <section>
		<title>Dan Armak</title>
		<body><p>Dan Armak is in charge of all things KDE for Gentoo Linux.  Here's a snapshot of his KDE-3.0_beta1 desktop, along with Hebrew support:</p>
		<fig link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-danarmak-small.jpg" linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-danarmak.html"/>
		</body>
	</section>

    <section>
		<title>Grant Goodyear</title>
		<body><p>Grant Goodyear (aka g2boojum) is a Gentoo Linux developer and a help to many in need.  Here's a snapshot of Grant's busy KDE 2.2.2 desktop:</p>
		<fig link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-g2boojum-small.jpg" linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-g2boojum.html"/>
		</body>
	</section>
    
	<section>
		<title>Geert Bevin</title>
		<body><p>Here's a shot of Geert Bevin's 1600x1200 desktop, running sawfish with the sawfish-merlin extensions which provide the pager and the iconbox:
		</p>
		<fig link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-gbevin-small.jpg" linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-gbevin.html"/>
		</body>
	</section>

         <section>
		<title>Ferry Meyndert</title>
		<body><p>Ferry Meyndert (M0rpheus) is responsible for the security work for Gentoo Linux. Here's my 1280x1024 GNOME2 desktop:
		</p>
		<fig link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-m0rpheus-small.jpg" linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-m0rpheus.html"/>
		</body>
	</section>
        <section>
		<title>Michael Joseph Cohen</title>
			<body><p>Michael Joseph Cohen is our kernel developer and a general bugtester.  He's pretty fond of WindowMaker and GNOME1, with lots of transparency.
			</p>
			<fig link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-mjc-small.jpg" linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-mjc.html"/> 
		</body>
	</section>    	
	<section>
                <title>Gabriele Giorgetti</title>
                        <body><p>Here's a shot of Gabriele Giorgetti's (stroke) 1024x768 GNOME2 desktop, running Metacity and Nautilus with the Gorillaz theme.</p>
                        <fig link="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-stroke-small.jpg" linkto="http://www.ibiblio.org/pub/Linux/distributions/gentoo/images/shots/desktop-stroke.html"/> 
		</body>
	</section>	
